4\cos^2(x)-4\sin(x)-5=0
(6\pi, 8\pi)
4y^2-4y -9 = 0
\cos x = 
\begin{align} 4\cos^2 x - 4\sin x - 5 & = 0 \\ \\\iff 4(1 - \sin^2 x) & = 4\sin x + 5 \\ \\  \iff 4\sin^2 x + 4\sin x + 1 &= 0\end{align}
\begin{align} y = \sin x \implies 4y^2 + 4y + 1 & = 0 \\ \\ (2y+1)^2 & = 0 \\ \\ \implies y & = -1/2\end{align}
y = \sin x = -1/2 \implies x = \sin^{-1}(-1/2) = 7\pi/6, 11\pi/6
x \in (0, 2\pi).
